<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Oil Pan, Vibration Damper, Oil
        Pump Water Pump, And Front Cover - Installation - Vibration Damper
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Vibration Damper</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply RTV sealant to the vibration damper keyway. This prevents oil seepage through damper
                keyway. Align the keyway in the damper with the key on the crankshaft and install the damper.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200531" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figF07/F0710.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Vibration Damper Installation Tool</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Installer Plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration Damper</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Forcing Nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>ZTSE4310 is a combination tool. One side is used to install the front oil seal while the other
                    side is used to install the vibration damper.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the puller screw, installer plate, thrust washer and nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn nut to draw the vibration damper onto the crankshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the installation tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200532" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1424.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Securing the Vibration Damper to the Crankshaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration Damper</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply RTV sealant to the washer and underside of the bolt head. Install the washer and
                mounting bolt. Tighten the bolt to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
